The Kenya National Highways Authority has thrown its weight behind the selection of US firm Bechtel International Inc to construct a 473-kilometre high-speed expressway between Nairobi and Mombasa.Kenha director general Peter Mundinia yesterday said in a statement that the firm was selected following its experience in handling large infrastructure.&acirc;&#128;&#156;The Kenyan government entered into an agreement with the US government in July 2015 to bring US companies to assist Kenya in development of key infrastructure projects and to utilise US agencies&acirc;&#128;&#153; financial support,&acirc;&#128;&#157; he said.Mundinia&acirc;&#128;&#153;s statement comes amid reports that the Sh300 billion project had sparked a fresh tender row among implementing agencies. He said Bechtel has experience in huge projects spanning 119 years.